In this week’s episode of the Major Issues Podcast, we dive webs-first into the brand-new animated series Your Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man! Join us as we break down Season 1 of Peter Parker’s latest adventure, exploring what sets this version apart from past Spidey stories. From fresh takes on iconic characters like Norman Osborn and Nico Minoru to the grounded tone and unique animation style, we analyze what worked, what didn’t, and what we’re hoping to see in future seasons. Is this show the perfect jumping-on point for new fans, or just another trip through the Spider-Verse? Tune in as we thwip through all ten episodes with great power and even greater opinions!

Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

